Hi Rhonda,

You can fix your version in your local repo. Just try to amend your commit if your version bump is in the most recent commit.

You can try,

	"git commit --amend"

This will allow you to fix your version number and try to push again.

It hasn?t changed on the server side (git.bioconductor.org) as the pre-receive hook prevents the commit with bad version coming in.

Best,

Nitesh 


